ew Maico Audiological Services’ Terms of Use — rules for site usage, privacy & liability. Read now to stay informed and use the site with confidence."}','01KS5S2H9D5GVDNPH6HQ00BNCN','2026-05-22 06:13:51');
INSERT INTO "revisions" ("id","collection","entry_id","data","author_id","created_at") VALUES('01KS69M9J84C4MQMMR5B7B78D7','utility_pages','01KS69M9J8BP07S9CZWYR5E5BS','{"title": "Insurance and Billing FAQs", "content": [{"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j81h0589051dvrbqfa", "style": "normal", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j86pzep1yb34r91f05", "text": "At Maico Audiological Services, we are dedicated to helping patients in Newport News, Chesapeake, and Smithfield, VA find the right hearing aids at affordable prices. In addition to offering a wide variety of hearing aids to fit every budget, we provide flexible payment options, including insurance, credit cards, and financing plans. Our goal is to make better hearing accessible to everyone.", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j809v27262yqm5z3fv", "style": "h2", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j8nbjq34nrajjqyfp2", "text": "Using Insurance to Pay for Hearing Aids", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8p5ea3bw9b4stdj4d", "style": "normal", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j847yc0kmn0dx42p2m", "text": "We accept a wide variety of insurance plans and have a dedicated team of insurance experts who will verify your benefits prior to your appointment. This ensures you clearly understand your coverage and all available options at the time of your visit.", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8s8a9v31jacvmwc6n", "style": "h2", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j8fj4mhynw5qx1vmc7", "text": "Hearing Aid Financing Options", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8my6bvqf2c91444fp", "style": "h3", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j82dv71djbekaxreh6", "text": "CareCredit®", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8gx9f13w89qs56j3k", "style": "normal", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j8x6xmbcmc5c438sfr", "text": "We proudly accept CareCredit, a healthcare credit card designed for medical expenses, including hearing services, hearing tests, and hearing aids. CareCredit offers special financing options, helping you spread payments over time for costs not covered by insurance.", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8knxyk6h2mgrak0ww", "style": "h3", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j8advtx4gbwct50j9p", "text": "Allegro Credit®", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8587k7sxxzst7j6ar", "style": "normal", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j85k7p3xyp6szpzqez", "text": "We also accept Allegro Credit, which provides flexible payment plans without application fees, prepayment penalties, or hidden charges. This option makes financing your hearing aids simple and transparent.", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8qkperafgtxs8f1n8", "style": "h2", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j8d669xzc4hk09b9t1", "text": "Find the Best Payment Option for You", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8w73v5we9avhyt9kt", "style": "normal", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j8wzs71r4jmdwcr2mb", "text": "Whether through insurance, credit card, or financing, our team is here to help you choose the best payment method for your needs. We’re committed to making hearing care affordable and accessible so you never miss out on life’s important moments.", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j85z6yz5kjqakew6fp", "style": "normal", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j83cdkyqzqtj3jjt5t", "text": "Call or text us today to explore your coverage and payment options.", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8kyj4e568we22gnts", "style": "h2", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j8x8pm4m9sw91qz17z", "text": "Questions? We’re Here to Help!", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8nk9gqcbm1ykqack4", "style": "normal", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j8caaxcn0edqywar4z", "text": "If you have any questions about your insurance, billing, or financing options, don’t hesitate to contact us. ", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}, {"_type": "block", "_key": "01ks69m9j8zzqfw5aytm1aps6e", "style": "normal", "children": [{"_type": "span", "_key": "01ks69m9j8h26hp34a760ssmv4", "text": "Call us today to learn more or to schedule an appointment!", "marks": []}], "markDefs": []}], "meta_title": "Insurance and Billing | Maico Audiological Services", "meta_description": "Learn more about Maico Audiological Services accepted insurance plans, billing, and payments."}','01KS5S2H9D5GVDNPH6HQ00BNCN','2026-05-22 06:13:51');
INSERT INTO "revisions" ("id","collection","entry_id","data","author_id","created_at") VALUES('01KS6BW614XWKM2CS7G462SZ15','blog_post','01KS5Y1MHVADNDT5BMBYJ9CKZT','{"title":"Hearing Aids for Tinnitus: How They Help You Find Relief and Hear Better","publish_date":"December 10, 2025","author":"Tracey E. Hudson, Au.D., CCC-A","category":"Hearing","content":[{"_type":"block","_key":"b002450","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002449","text":"Tinnitus can sound like ringing, buzzing, or hissing in your ears, and it can make daily life stressful. Hearing aids for tinnitus can help by making real sounds louder, which can make the tinnitus less noticeable. In this article, you’ll learn how tinnitus works, how hearing aids can help, what features to look for, and how Maico Audiology supports patients in Newport News, Smithfield, and Chesapeake, VA.","marks":["strong","em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002455","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002451","text":"If you are tired of the constant ringing or buzzing in your ears, you may be wondering if hearing aids for tinnitus can help. The answer is often yes, especially when tinnitus is linked to hearing loss, which is very common."},{"_type":"span","_key":"s002453","text":"Hearing aids","marks":["m002452"]},{"_type":"span","_key":"s002454","text":"do not “cure” tinnitus, but they can reduce how loud it feels and how much it bothers you. They do this by improving your hearing, lowering listening stress, and sometimes adding special relief sounds."}],"markDefs":[{"_type":"link","_key":"m002452","href":"/hearing-aids-products/"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002457","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002456","text":"At Maico Audiology, we help people of all ages better understand tinnitus and find solutions that fit their daily life. With the right evaluation and a personalized plan, many patients feel calmer, sleep better, and enjoy conversations again."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002459","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002458","text":"What Is Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002461","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002460","text":"Tinnitus is when you hear a sound that is not coming from the outside world. Many people describe it as:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002463","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002462","text":"Ringing"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002465","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002464","text":"Buzzing"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002467","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002466","text":"Hissing"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002469","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002468","text":"Clicking"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002471","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002470","text":"Roaring"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002473","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002472","text":"Whooshing"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002475","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002474","text":"Tinnitus can be soft or loud. It can come and go, or it can be there all the time. Some people hear it in one ear, while others hear it in both."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002477","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002476","text":"Tinnitus is not a disease by itself. It is usually a symptom of something else, like hearing loss, noise exposure, stress, or a medical condition."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002479","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002478","text":"Why Do People Get Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002481","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002480","text":"Tinnitus has many possible causes. Some of the most common include:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002483","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002482","text":"Hearing Loss"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002485","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002484","text":"This is the biggest reason tinnitus happens. When the ear does not send strong sound signals to the brain, the brain may “fill in the gaps” with tinnitus sounds."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002487","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002486","text":"Loud Noise Exposure"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002489","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002488","text":"Concerts, power tools, firearms, and loud workplaces can damage hearing over time. Even one very loud sound can trigger tinnitus."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002491","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002490","text":"Earwax Buildup"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002493","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002492","text":"A blockage can change how sound travels through the ear, making tinnitus more noticeable."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002495","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002494","text":"Ear Infections or Fluid"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002497","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002496","text":"Inflammation can irritate the ear and increase tinnitus."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002499","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002498","text":"Certain Medications"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002501","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002500","text":"Some medicines can affect the inner ear. Never stop medication without talking to your doctor."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002503","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002502","text":"Stress and Poor Sleep"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002505","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002504","text":"Stress can make tinnitus feel louder. Poor sleep can make it harder to cope."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002507","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002506","text":"Jaw Problems (TMJ)"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002509","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002508","text":"Jaw tension can sometimes affect the ear and cause tinnitus-like symptoms."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002511","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002510","text":"Because tinnitus can have many causes, the best first step is a professional hearing evaluation."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002513","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002512","text":"Do Hearing Aids Help Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002515","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002514","text":"Yes, for many people, hearing aids for tinnitus are one of the most helpful tools available—especially if you also have hearing loss (even mild hearing loss)."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002517","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002516","text":"Here’s why hearing aids often work:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002519","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002518","text":"1. They Make Real Sounds Louder"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002521","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002520","text":"When you hear more of the world around you (voices, footsteps, birds, fans), your tinnitus can fade into the background."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002523","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002522","text":"2. They Reduce Listening Strain"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002525","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002524","text":"When your brain works less to “guess” what people are saying, your stress level often goes down. Lower stress can make tinnitus feel quieter."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002527","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002526","text":"3. They Improve Focus"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002529","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002528","text":"Hearing aids help you focus on speech instead of the ringing. This can make tinnitus less distracting in daily life."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002531","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002530","text":"4. Many Have Built-In Tinnitus Relief Sounds"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002533","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002532","text":"Some hearing aids can play soft relief sounds, like:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002535","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002534","text":"White noise"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002537","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002536","text":"Ocean-like sounds"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002539","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002538","text":"Gentle static or “shhh” sounds"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002541","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002540","text":"Nature sounds"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002543","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002542","text":"These are often called masking sounds or sound therapy features."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002545","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002544","text":"How Hearing Aids Work For Tinnitus"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002547","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002546","text":"Masking does not mean “covering tinnitus so you can’t hear it at all.” Instead, it gives your brain another sound to pay attention to. This can make tinnitus feel less sharp or less annoying."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002549","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002548","text":"Think of it like this:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002551","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002550","text":"In a silent room, tinnitus may stand out."}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002553","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002552","text":"In a room with calm background sound, tinnitus may blend in."}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002555","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002554","text":"Hearing aids for tinnitus aim to create a comfortable sound environment so tinnitus bothers you less."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002557","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002556","text":"Who Is a Good Candidate for Hearing Aids for Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002559","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002558","text":"You may be a good match if:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002561","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002560","text":"You have tinnitus and also struggle to hear speech clearly"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002563","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002562","text":"You turn up the TV more than others do"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002565","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002564","text":"You have trouble hearing in restaurants"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002567","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002566","text":"You feel tired after conversations"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002569","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002568","text":"Your hearing test shows mild, moderate, or greater hearing loss"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002571","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002570","text":"Even if your hearing loss is mild, hearing aids may still help reduce tinnitus stress."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002573","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002572","text":"Not sure? That’s normal. A hearing test can give you clarity."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002575","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002574","text":"What Features Should You Look for in Hearing Aids for Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002577","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002576","text":"If tinnitus relief is a goal, these features can help:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002579","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002578","text":"Tinnitus Sound Support / Sound Generator"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002581","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002580","text":"This feature plays masking sounds or calming tones."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002583","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002582","text":"Good Noise Management"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002585","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002584","text":"Background noise can make tinnitus feel worse. Hearing aids with strong noise handling can help speech feel clearer."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002587","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002586","text":"Directional Microphones"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002589","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002588","text":"These help you focus on the person speaking in front of you."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002591","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002590","text":"Bluetooth Connectivity"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002593","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002592","text":"You can stream calming sounds, music, or guided relaxation from your phone."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002595","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002594","text":"App Controls"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002597","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002596","text":"Many people like adjusting volume or tinnitus settings from a smartphone app."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002599","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002598","text":"Comfortable Fit"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002601","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002600","text":"If the hearing aid feels uncomfortable, you may not wear it enough. Comfort matters for long-term success."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002603","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002602","text":"At Maico Audiology, we match features to your lifestyle, not just your hearing test."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002605","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002604","text":"What to Expect at a Tinnitus Appointment"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002607","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002606","text":"A tinnitus visit is not just “pick a hearing aid.” The goal is to understand what is happening and build a plan that works for you."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002609","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002608","text":"Step 1: Getting to Know You"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002611","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002610","text":"We ask questions like:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002613","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002612","text":"When did tinnitus start?"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002615","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002614","text":"Is it in one ear or both?"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002617","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002616","text":"Is it constant or off and on?"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002619","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002618","text":"What makes it worse or better?"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002621","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002620","text":"How is your sleep?"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002623","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002622","text":"How is your stress?"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002625","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002624","text":"Any noise exposure history?"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002627","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002626","text":"Step 2: Ear Exam"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002629","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002628","text":"We check for:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002631","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002630","text":"Earwax buildup"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002633","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002632","text":"Signs of infection"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002635","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002634","text":"Blockage or irritation"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002637","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002636","text":"Step 3: Hearing Testing"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002639","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002638","text":"A hearing test helps us see if hearing loss is part of the picture. This matters because hearing loss is one of the top reasons tinnitus happens."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002641","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002640","text":"Step 4: A Clear Plan"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002643","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002642","text":"If hearing aids are a good fit, we explain options. If something else seems likely, we may recommend medical follow-up, too."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002645","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002644","text":"How Hearing Aids Are Fitted for Tinnitus"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002647","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002646","text":"If you choose hearing aids, fitting is important. Hearing aids must be adjusted to your hearing needs and your comfort."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002649","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002648","text":"During your fitting, you can expect:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002651","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002650","text":"Programming based on your hearing test"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002653","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002652","text":"Comfort checks (so nothing feels too tight)"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002655","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002654","text":"Feedback checks (to prevent whistling)"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002657","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002656","text":"Tinnitus feature setup if your devices include it"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002659","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002658","text":"Real-life listening tips for home and work"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002661","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002660","text":"Then we schedule follow-ups because tinnitus relief and hearing comfort often improve with small fine-tuning changes."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002663","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002662","text":"How Long Does It Take to Adjust?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002665","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002664","text":"Many people notice changes quickly, sometimes the same day. But adjustment can take time, too."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002667","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002666","text":"It is normal if:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002669","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002668","text":"Your own voice sounds different at first"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002671","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002670","text":"Every day sounds seem sharper"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002673","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002672","text":"You need a few follow-ups to fine-tune settings"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002675","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002674","text":"Your brain is learning how to process clearer sound again. With consistent wear, most people adapt well."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002677","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002676","text":"Other Helpful Tools Alongside Hearing Aids"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002679","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002678","text":"Hearing aids can be a big help, but tinnitus care often works best as a “toolbox.” Other tools may include:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002681","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002680","text":"Sound Enrichment at Night"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002683","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002682","text":"A fan, white noise machine, or soft sound app can make bedtime easier."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002685","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002684","text":"Stress Management"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002687","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002686","text":"Stress can increase tinnitus. Simple steps like breathing exercises, walking, or gentle stretching can help."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002689","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002688","text":"Better Sleep Habits"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002691","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002690","text":"Poor sleep makes tinnitus feel louder. A steady bedtime routine can reduce tinnitus distress."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002693","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002692","text":"Hearing Protection"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002695","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002694","text":"Protect your ears from loud sounds. Hearing protection is important, but wearing earplugs all day in normal sound can sometimes make tinnitus feel louder. We can guide you on smart use."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002697","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002696","text":"Medical Referral When Needed"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002699","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002698","text":"If tinnitus is sudden, only in one ear, comes with dizziness, or seems pulse-like, you should get a medical evaluation. We can help guide you for the next steps."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002701","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002700","text":"Common Questions People Ask About Hearing Aids for Tinnitus"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002703","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002702","text":"Will hearing aids stop tinnitus completely?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002705","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002704","text":"Not always. But many people notice tinnitus is less noticeable and less stressful when they hear better and use sound therapy features."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002707","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002706","text":"What if I only have tinnitus and no hearing loss?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002709","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002708","text":"Some people still benefit from sound therapy devices or counseling strategies. A hearing test helps decide the best option."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002711","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002710","text":"Do I have to wear hearing aids all day for tinnitus relief?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002713","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002712","text":"Most people get the best results with regular wear. The more your brain gets steady sound input, the better tinnitus blending usually works."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002715","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002714","text":"Can hearing aids make tinnitus worse?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002717","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002716","text":"When fitted correctly, they should not. Poor programming or overly loud settings can cause discomfort, which is why professional fitting and follow-up matter."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002719","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002718","text":"When You Should Get Help Right Away"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002721","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002720","text":"While tinnitus is often not dangerous, contact a healthcare provider promptly if you have:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002723","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002722","text":"Sudden hearing loss"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002725","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002724","text":"Tinnitus in only one ear that is new"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002727","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002726","text":"Severe dizziness or spinning"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002729","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002728","text":"Ear pain, drainage, or fever"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002731","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002730","text":"A pulsing sound that matches your heartbeat"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002733","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002732","text":"These symptoms can signal issues that need medical evaluation."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002735","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002734","text":"Why Choose Maico Audiology in Virginia?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002737","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002736","text":"At Maico Audiology, we believe tinnitus care should feel personal, calm, and clear. We help patients:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002739","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002738","text":"Understand what tinnitus means for their hearing health"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002741","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002740","text":"Get accurate testing and answers"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002743","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002742","text":"Explore hearing aids with tinnitus relief options"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002745","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002744","text":"Learn simple daily strategies that make tinnitus easier to live with"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002747","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002746","text":"Get follow-up care and ongoing support"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002749","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002748","text":"We proudly serve patients in Newport News, Smithfield, and Chesapeake, VA, and we’re here to guide you step by step."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002751","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002750","text":"A Simple Next Step"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002753","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002752","text":"Tinnitus can be exhausting. It can interrupt sleep, make quiet moments feel stressful, and make it harder to focus. The good news is you do not have to figure it out alone. With the right plan, many people feel real improvement."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002755","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002754","text":"If you are ready to explore hearing aids for tinnitus, start with a professional hearing evaluation. The right information leads to the right solution. At Maico Audiology, we’ll listen to your concerns, explain your results in a clear way, and help you choose the best path forward."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b002760","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s002756","text":"And remember: hearing aids for tinnitus are not just about sound. They are about comfort, confidence, and feeling more like yourself again."},{"_type":"span","_key":"s002758","text":"Schedule an appointment","marks":["m002757"]},{"_type":"span","_key":"s002759","text":"today!"}],"markDefs":[{"_type":"link","_key":"m002757","href":"/book-appointment/"}]}],"featured_image":{"id":"01KS5SXCHRG7NVSX295207XD5H","alt":"","provider":"local","filename":"assets__media__Hearing-Aids-for-Tinnitus-How-They-Help-You-Find-Relief-and-Hear-Better-08101a26a3.jpg","mimeType":"image/jpeg","meta":{"storageKey":"01KS5SXCF3QFE8J8R6RRKARNTV.jpg","caption":null,"blurhash":"LiNw1hRj-p%2~Ct7J7jtNbayjFWU","dominantColor":"rgb(194,190,191)"}},"meta_title":"Hearing Aids for Tinnitus | Maico Audiological Services","meta_description":"Hearing aids for tinnitus can improve hearing and help reduce ringing in the ears. Visit Maico Audiology to connect with expert audiologists in Virginia.","_slug":"hearing-aids-for-tinnitus"}',NULL,'2026-05-21 22:53:07');
INSERT INTO "revisions" ("id","collection","entry_id","data","author_id","created_at") VALUES('01KS6BX11CV0WTB1HTJCVR6H5S','blog_post','01KS5Y1MNXG5CF0XFF7476JCPT','{"title":"Understanding Swimmer’s Ear: Causes, Symptoms, and Safe Treatment","publish_date":"November 13, 2025","author":"Tracey E. Hudson, Au.D., CCC-A","category":"Hearing","content":[{"_type":"block","_key":"b003464","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003460","text":"Swimmer’s ear is a painful and uncomfortable condition that can cause itchiness, drainage, and hearing changes after water gets trapped in the ear canal. It often affects people who spend time in the water, but anyone can develop it. At Maico Audiological Services, with offices in Newport News, Smithfield, and Chesapeake, VA, our audiologists help patients find relief from swimmer’s ear and other hearing concerns through","marks":["strong","em"]},{"_type":"span","_key":"s003462","text":"hearing tests","marks":["m003461","strong","em"]},{"_type":"span","_key":"s003463","text":", prevention tips, and professional guidance.","marks":["strong","em"]}],"markDefs":[{"_type":"link","_key":"m003461","href":"/audiology-services/hearing-tests/"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003466","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003465","text":"What Is Swimmer’s Ear?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003468","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003467","text":"Swimmer’s ear, also known as otitis externa, is an infection or inflammation of the outer ear canal-the passage that runs from the outside of your ear to your eardrum. It usually occurs when water stays trapped inside the ear after swimming, showering, or bathing. This trapped moisture creates the perfect environment for bacteria or fungi to grow."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003470","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003469","text":"Although the name “swimmer’s ear” might make you think it only affects swimmers, that’s not always the case. It can happen to anyone exposed to moisture or humidity for extended periods. Even activities like sweating heavily or cleaning your ears too often can make the ear canal more vulnerable."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003472","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003471","text":"Audiologists often see patients, both frequent swimmers and non-swimmers, who develop itchiness, pain, or fullness in the ear after water exposure. Understanding what causes it can help you take steps to prevent it."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003474","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003473","text":"What Causes Swimmer’s Ear?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003476","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003475","text":"Swimmer’s ear develops when moisture, injury, or irritation disrupts the natural protective layer inside your ear canal. Once that protective barrier breaks down, bacteria or fungi can grow and lead to infection."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003478","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003477","text":"Here are the most common causes and risk factors:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003480","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003479","text":"1. Water Exposure","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003482","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003481","text":"When water remains trapped in your ear canal after swimming, showering, or bathing, it increases humidity inside the ear. This warm, damp environment helps bacteria or fungi multiply."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003484","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003483","text":"2. Ear Canal Injury","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003486","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003485","text":"Inserting cotton swabs, fingers, or small objects into your ear can scratch the delicate skin, making it easier for germs to enter. Even minor irritation can trigger an infection."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003488","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003487","text":"3. Earwax Problems","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003490","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003489","text":"Earwax plays an important role in ear health by acting as a natural barrier against dirt and bacteria. Removing too much wax can leave your ear unprotected, while excess wax can trap water inside and cause swimmer’s ear."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003492","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003491","text":"4. Climate and Humidity","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003494","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003493","text":"People who live in warm, moist areas or spend time in high humidity are more likely to develop swimmer’s ear, even if they aren’t swimmers. Moist air prevents the ear canal from drying properly."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003496","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003495","text":"5. Skin Conditions","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003498","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003497","text":"Those with eczema, psoriasis, or chronic allergies may have dry or flaky skin, which can lead to itchiness and small cracks in the ear canal, allowing bacteria to enter more easily."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003500","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003499","text":"Symptoms of Swimmer’s Ear"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003502","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003501","text":"The symptoms of swimmer’s ear can range from mild irritation to severe pain. Recognizing them early helps you get the right treatment before complications occur."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003504","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003503","text":"Common signs include:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003506","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003505","text":"Itchiness inside the ear canal (one of the earliest symptoms)"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003508","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003507","text":"Ear pain that worsens when pulling on the ear or moving the jaw"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003510","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003509","text":"Fullness or pressure in the ear"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003512","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003511","text":"Redness or swelling around the outer ear"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003514","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003513","text":"Fluid drainage, which may be clear, yellow, or pus-like"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003516","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003515","text":"Muffled hearing or a sensation that the ear is “blocked”"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003518","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003517","text":"Tenderness when touching the ear or surrounding area"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003520","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003519","text":"Fever or swollen glands near the ear (in advanced cases)"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003522","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003521","text":"If left untreated, swimmer’s ear can cause more severe infection or temporary hearing loss. That’s why seeing an audiologist or doctor promptly is important when symptoms persist."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003527","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003523","text":"Maico Audiological Services connects you to an expert"},{"_type":"span","_key":"s003525","text":"audiologist in Newport News, VA","marks":["m003524"]},{"_type":"span","_key":"s003526","text":", Chesapeake, VA, and Smithfield, VA."}],"markDefs":[{"_type":"link","_key":"m003524","href":"/audiologist-hearing-aids-newport-news-va/"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003529","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003528","text":"How Swimmer’s Ear Is Diagnosed"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003531","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003530","text":"Diagnosing swimmer’s ear is simple, gentle, and pain-free. Here’s an overview:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003533","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003532","text":"Medical History:","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003535","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003534","text":"We’ll ask about recent water exposure, ear symptoms, or prior infections. Ear Examination:","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003537","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003536","text":"Using a lighted tool called an otoscope, your audiologist will look inside the ear canal for redness, swelling, wax, or fluid buildup."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003539","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003538","text":"Cleaning (if needed):","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003541","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003540","text":"If wax or debris is blocking the view, we may safely remove it for a clearer examination. If the infection looks severe or involves deeper tissue, your audiologist may refer you to your doctor or an ear, nose, and throat specialist for additional care."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003543","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003542","text":"Treatment for Swimmer’s Ear"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003545","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003544","text":"Treatment for swimmer’s ear focuses on clearing the infection, reducing itchiness and pain, and helping the ear heal. Most cases resolve quickly with the right care."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003547","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003546","text":"1. Cleaning the Ear Canal","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003549","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003548","text":"Gently removing debris or excess wax helps medications work better. Our Smithfield, VA audiologists at Maico Audiological Services use professional tools to clean the ear safely, avoiding further irritation."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003551","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003550","text":"2. Prescription Ear Drops","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003553","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003552","text":"Antibiotic ear drops are the most common treatment for swimmer’s ear. They fight bacteria and may include a mild steroid to reduce inflammation and itching. It’s important to use them exactly as prescribed. If your infection is caused by a fungus, antifungal drops may be used instead."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003555","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003554","text":"3. Oral Antibiotics","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003557","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003556","text":"In more serious infections or cases where the infection spreads beyond the ear canal, your doctor may prescribe oral antibiotics to help your body fight the infection from within."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003559","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003558","text":"4. Pain and Inflammation Relief","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003561","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003560","text":"Over-the-counter pain relievers like acetaminophen or ibuprofen can reduce discomfort while the infection heals."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003563","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003562","text":"5. Keeping the Ear Dry","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003565","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003564","text":"Avoid swimming, diving, or soaking your ears during treatment. When showering, protect the ear with a soft earplug or cotton ball lightly coated with petroleum jelly. With the right treatment and follow-up, most patients start feeling relief within a few days."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003567","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003566","text":"Prevention: How to Avoid Swimmer’s Ear"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003569","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003568","text":"Preventing swimmer’s ear is often easier than treating it. A few simple habits can protect your ears and reduce the risk of infection."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003571","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003570","text":"1. Keep Your Ears Dry","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003573","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003572","text":"After swimming or bathing, gently tilt your head to each side to let water drain. Pat your outer ear dry with a towel-don’t insert anything into the canal."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003575","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003574","text":"2. Protect Ears While Swimming","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003577","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003576","text":"Frequent swimmers can benefit from custom-fitted swim earplugs, available through our offices in Newport News, Smithfield, and Chesapeake, VA. These keep water out while maintaining comfort and sound clarity."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003579","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003578","text":"3. Avoid Overcleaning","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003581","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003580","text":"Cleaning too deeply removes protective earwax and increases the risk of itchiness and infection. If you feel blocked, visit an audiologist for professional cleaning."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003583","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003582","text":"4. Manage Humidity and Sweat","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003585","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003584","text":"If you live in a high-humidity area or sweat frequently, let your ears air out after exercise or outdoor activities. Wearing breathable headgear can also help reduce trapped moisture."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003587","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003586","text":"5. Use Preventive Drops","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003589","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003588","text":"Ask your audiologist or doctor about safe, over-the-counter drying drops to use after swimming. These help remove leftover moisture and prevent bacterial growth."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003591","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003590","text":"When to See an Audiologist or Doctor"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003593","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003592","text":"While mild cases can improve with home care, persistent symptoms should be evaluated by a professional."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003595","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003594","text":"You should schedule an appointment if you experience:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003597","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003596","text":"Ongoing itchiness or ear pain"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003599","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003598","text":"Drainage or swelling that worsens"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003601","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003600","text":"Reduced or muffled hearing"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003603","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003602","text":"A feeling of fullness or blockage"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003605","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003604","text":"Fever or spreading redness"}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003607","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003606","text":"At Maico Audiological Services, we’ll determine whether your swimmer’s ear is caused by bacteria, fungus, or another issue, and we’ll recommend safe, effective treatment options."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003609","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003608","text":"Living Comfortably After Swimmer’s Ear"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003611","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003610","text":"Once your ear heals, it’s important to protect it from future infections."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003613","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003612","text":"Here’s how:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003615","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003614","text":"Keep your ears clean but avoid inserting objects into them."}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003617","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003616","text":"Dry your ears after every swim or shower."}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003619","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003618","text":"Treat colds, allergies, and sinus congestion early to prevent Eustachian tube problems."}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003621","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003620","text":"Be mindful of humidity, especially during summer months or in moist environments."}],"listItem":"bullet","level":1},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003623","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003622","text":"Our team at Maico Audiological Services is here to help you maintain ear comfort and hearing wellness year-round."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003625","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003624","text":"Frequently Asked Questions"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003627","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003626","text":"Is swimmer’s ear contagious?","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003629","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003628","text":"No, swimmer’s ear is not contagious. It’s caused by bacteria or fungi that grow inside a person’s ear canal, usually because of trapped water, irritation, or too much moisture. You can’t catch it from swimming near someone with an infection or sharing water."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003631","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003630","text":"However, if you share earbuds, towels, or earplugs, you could spread bacteria that may increase the risk of infection. Keeping ears clean and dry helps prevent it from developing."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003633","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003632","text":"How long does swimmer’s ear last?","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003635","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003634","text":"With proper treatment, swimmer’s ear usually starts improving within a few days and clears up completely in 7 to 10 days. The length of recovery depends on how severe the infection is and how quickly treatment begins. Using prescribed antibiotic ear drops as directed by your doctor and keeping your ear dry during healing can help it clear faster. If symptoms, such as itchiness, pain, or drainage, don’t improve after a week, follow up with your audiologist or healthcare provider for another evaluation."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003637","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003636","text":"What happens if swimmer’s ear goes untreated?","marks":["em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003639","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003638","text":"If swimmer’s ear is left untreated, the infection can worsen and spread deeper into the ear canal or surrounding tissue. This may cause increased pain, swelling, earache, or even temporary hearing loss. In severe cases, the infection could reach nearby bones or lymph nodes, requiring stronger antibiotics or medical intervention. Early treatment is the best remedy. It relieves symptoms faster and prevents complications. If you notice persistent discomfort, drainage, or hearing changes, schedule a consultation with an audiologist or doctor as soon as possible."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003641","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003640","text":"Expert Audiologists in Virginia"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003643","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003642","text":"If you’re struggling with swimmer’s ear, don’t wait for symptoms to worsen. The earlier you seek treatment, the easier it is to relieve pain, stop itchiness, and prevent infection from spreading."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003648","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003644","text":"At"},{"_type":"span","_key":"s003646","text":"Maico Audiological Services","marks":["m003645"]},{"_type":"span","_key":"s003647","text":", we proudly serve the communities of Newport News, Smithfield, and Chesapeake, VA, providing compassionate care for patients of all ages. Whether you’re an active swimmer or simply someone experiencing ear discomfort, our experienced audiologists can help."}],"markDefs":[{"_type":"link","_key":"m003645","href":"/"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003650","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003649","text":"We offer professional ear examinations, safe ear cleanings, and guidance on treatment options, including when to see your doctor for antibiotics or additional care."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b003652","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s003651","text":"Call Maico Audiological Services today to schedule your appointment. With expert care, preventive strategies, and personalized support, you can recover from swimmer’s ear quickly and get back to enjoying the water comfortably and safely."}]}],"featured_image":{"id":"01KS5SXTXQT8DF8BN2RM3H51KW","alt":"","provider":"local","filename":"assets__media__Understanding-Swimmers-Ear-Causes-Symptoms-and-Safe-Treatment-1bdfec1919.jpg","mimeType":"image/jpeg","meta":{"storageKey":"01KS5SXTVNQE1G4ECJ0GMXHBCN.jpg","caption":null,"blurhash":"L9GT4[.m00E,v-?b57%2DiWF$e-6","dominantColor":"rgb(132,164,167)"}},"meta_title":"Understanding Swimmer''s Ear: Causes, Symptoms, and Safe Treatment | Maico Audiological Services","meta_description":"If you’re struggling with swimmer’s ear, don’t wait for symptoms to worsen. Call Maico Audiological Services today to schedule your appointment with an audiologist.","_slug":"swimmers-ear"}',NULL,'2026-05-21 22:53:34');
INSERT INTO "revisions" ("id","collection","entry_id","data","author_id","created_at") VALUES('01KS6BYBCMGR7DZN0QER8JRZ38','blog_post','01KS5Y1MHVADNDT5BMBYJ9CKZT','{"title":"Hearing Aids for Tinnitus: How They Help You Find Relief and Hear Better","publish_date":"December 10, 2025","author":"Tracey E. Hudson, Au.D., CCC-A","category":"Hearing","content":[{"_type":"block","_key":"9u5gqzwvs","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"nrk2g1672","text":"Tinnitus can sound like ringing, buzzing, or hissing in your ears, and it can make daily life stressful. Hearing aids for tinnitus can help by making real sounds louder, which can make the tinnitus less noticeable. In this article, you’ll learn how tinnitus works, how hearing aids can help, what features to look for, and how Maico Audiology supports patients in Newport News, Smithfield, and Chesapeake, VA.","marks":["strong","em"]}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"yj4fwg3yp","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"7z5zvyoth","text":"If you are tired of the constant ringing or buzzing in your ears, you may be wondering if hearing aids for tinnitus can help. The answer is often yes, especially when tinnitus is linked to hearing loss, which is very common. "},{"_type":"span","_key":"0pfv7jumt","text":"Hearing aids ","marks":["lp0jzktkz"]},{"_type":"span","_key":"2oklmpnp3","text":"do not “cure” tinnitus, but they can reduce how loud it feels and how much it bothers you. They do this by improving your hearing, lowering listening stress, and sometimes adding special relief sounds."}],"markDefs":[{"_type":"link","_key":"lp0jzktkz","href":"/hearing-aids-products/","blank":false}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"53tg2qe1i","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"2v3yolk09","text":"At Maico Audiology, we help people of all ages better understand tinnitus and find solutions that fit their daily life. With the right evaluation and a personalized plan, many patients feel calmer, sleep better, and enjoy conversations again."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"v2sd5f1a4","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"b7axkj2fm","text":"What Is Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"xgvo8n376","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"c74ffs59o","text":"Tinnitus is when you hear a sound that is not coming from the outside world. Many people describe it as:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"xn848olx2","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"kkwdkhv78","text":"Ringing"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"bpjrkmz6o","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"2d6d1ff7c","text":"Buzzing"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"ccdzmzfnk","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"zf8dsqnxp","text":"Hissing"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"6rnz6cn51","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"iqphugcqo","text":"Clicking"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"lnxmlktfl","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"j8pwjlizl","text":"Roaring"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"0b1ghfy26","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"tdva60thu","text":"Whooshing"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"ck1o91fg1","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"rlsvk61hn","text":"Tinnitus can be soft or loud. It can come and go, or it can be there all the time. Some people hear it in one ear, while others hear it in both."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"y3gv7fn8m","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"edd3dtacc","text":"Tinnitus is not a disease by itself. It is usually a symptom of something else, like hearing loss, noise exposure, stress, or a medical condition."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"v02p2pglq","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"ftyqbx3g3","text":"Why Do People Get Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"pqqgeku71","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"tggse38xh","text":"Tinnitus has many possible causes. Some of the most common include:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"8lf1ayk2l","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"23dwdf3fq","text":"Hearing Loss"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"7ggzf49n4","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"dv0eyk0q2","text":"This is the biggest reason tinnitus happens. When the ear does not send strong sound signals to the brain, the brain may “fill in the gaps” with tinnitus sounds."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"ecot363rf","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"907py0qo5","text":"Loud Noise Exposure"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"zyxjgs0of","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"h70npq21z","text":"Concerts, power tools, firearms, and loud workplaces can damage hearing over time. Even one very loud sound can trigger tinnitus."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"lj2itjejd","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"0bmni19o7","text":"Earwax Buildup"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"wfih8v969","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"62u65yvy1","text":"A blockage can change how sound travels through the ear, making tinnitus more noticeable."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"ium2lflv4","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"5imbl5w5a","text":"Ear Infections or Fluid"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"c32d460yu","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"7gge1lkum","text":"Inflammation can irritate the ear and increase tinnitus."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"d0oiewcn7","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"5npt6473u","text":"Certain Medications"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"epyi56l2m","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"79z2jaua5","text":"Some medicines can affect the inner ear. Never stop medication without talking to your doctor."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"fpo1vz2ji","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"0ira6lyc3","text":"Stress and Poor Sleep"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"2wvjufkek","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"smil9sq7t","text":"Stress can make tinnitus feel louder. Poor sleep can make it harder to cope."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"ujtppj2b9","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"qvyksosuv","text":"Jaw Problems (TMJ)"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"age1jhm65","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"akt06wkfn","text":"Jaw tension can sometimes affect the ear and cause tinnitus-like symptoms."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"oxd75cbtm","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"7jtrvyind","text":"Because tinnitus can have many causes, the best first step is a professional hearing evaluation."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"f8fbvzwql","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"xmrazg5xv","text":"Do Hearing Aids Help Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"payrzfhye","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"4ovy7227e","text":"Yes, for many people, hearing aids for tinnitus are one of the most helpful tools available—especially if you also have hearing loss (even mild hearing loss)."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"7ymnyeglq","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"riynaypg6","text":"Here’s why hearing aids often work:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"mjzp2u6ha","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"xrv9klkny","text":"1. They Make Real Sounds Louder"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"q97mt7cqt","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"341vyksme","text":"When you hear more of the world around you (voices, footsteps, birds, fans), your tinnitus can fade into the background."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"2cz9jxq1m","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"hiaw9wjx8","text":"2. They Reduce Listening Strain"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"qcpnbrzm9","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"pmmdqykpw","text":"When your brain works less to “guess” what people are saying, your stress level often goes down. Lower stress can make tinnitus feel quieter."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"x9kw9vfax","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"8js7xtx63","text":"3. They Improve Focus"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"9s01z6ikl","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"fgfd73dva","text":"Hearing aids help you focus on speech instead of the ringing. This can make tinnitus less distracting in daily life."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"eqkpuvxdp","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"6pjlxwaig","text":"4. Many Have Built-In Tinnitus Relief Sounds"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"0c97fz87g","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"t6v7eepqg","text":"Some hearing aids can play soft relief sounds, like:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"0cfiv6jre","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"jfgu00upc","text":"White noise"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"qq8ewtmm8","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"t9mou8m7h","text":"Ocean-like sounds"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"dzcf04pxr","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"dp01jsxtk","text":"Gentle static or “shhh” sounds"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"v8ovv28vo","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"w4g8e0nyi","text":"Nature sounds"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"11lzy1tus","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"8bjtlnfuo","text":"These are often called masking sounds or sound therapy features."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"cgyfod8gb","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"i4pairlfc","text":"How Hearing Aids Work For Tinnitus"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"b5zph8gwu","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"a0369hhrz","text":"Masking does not mean “covering tinnitus so you can’t hear it at all.” Instead, it gives your brain another sound to pay attention to. This can make tinnitus feel less sharp or less annoying."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"wr46ej4oz","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"i1jcjxi64","text":"Think of it like this:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"tqqquhio2","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"3m56o8h8s","text":"In a silent room, tinnitus may stand out."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"4cw1cz9lr","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"cspm9e4xz","text":"In a room with calm background sound, tinnitus may blend in."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"a25tg5fdo","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"9klr7uchx","text":"Hearing aids for tinnitus aim to create a comfortable sound environment so tinnitus bothers you less."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"8wayug6x7","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"8dm54fc5p","text":"Who Is a Good Candidate for Hearing Aids for Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"sa0u26uk9","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"3eul5p7n9","text":"You may be a good match if:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"8o7st514k","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"ulvo4ljmf","text":"You have tinnitus and also struggle to hear speech clearly"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"kg78mqbid","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"cnk7pmk96","text":"You turn up the TV more than others do"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"dmjevhoi6","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"whfoj6ism","text":"You have trouble hearing in restaurants"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"1xt1b6jzn","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"ja367dy8t","text":"You feel tired after conversations"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"lp9zyqzt3","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"em1q497qc","text":"Your hearing test shows mild, moderate, or greater hearing loss"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"jyowtws1e","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"ogdiz51c6","text":"Even if your hearing loss is mild, hearing aids may still help reduce tinnitus stress."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"1cw1zybgq","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"loj86dm5y","text":"Not sure? That’s normal. A hearing test can give you clarity."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"9nxikrtov","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"a89wdtrc8","text":"What Features Should You Look for in Hearing Aids for Tinnitus?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"gevta0xqf","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"g9jazuujl","text":"If tinnitus relief is a goal, these features can help:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"fls94fq7m","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"n2z1j4wzf","text":"Tinnitus Sound Support / Sound Generator"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"ix35kdvjh","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"yfs6uyr71","text":"This feature plays masking sounds or calming tones."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"c44oz7x1s","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"8f4z6s6ow","text":"Good Noise Management"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"3glq8tbyl","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"u4zqp67od","text":"Background noise can make tinnitus feel worse. Hearing aids with strong noise handling can help speech feel clearer."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"o8g5qk9ea","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"6283rn4u3","text":"Directional Microphones"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"vk8t7bo1o","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"7x70t3zf0","text":"These help you focus on the person speaking in front of you."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"k9kvtrxel","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"sg0igc9wd","text":"Bluetooth Connectivity"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"hixhu3xx0","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"zjtjpgsjo","text":"You can stream calming sounds, music, or guided relaxation from your phone."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"83p24iufi","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"kayp24n2x","text":"App Controls"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"36tc81edm","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"bm5ylw2rj","text":"Many people like adjusting volume or tinnitus settings from a smartphone app."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"6x29ooegl","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"gpgxby6ii","text":"Comfortable Fit"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"f8lncbidb","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"tpc5y9ezo","text":"If the hearing aid feels uncomfortable, you may not wear it enough. Comfort matters for long-term success."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"4taif2xkc","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"draa53ike","text":"At Maico Audiology, we match features to your lifestyle, not just your hearing test."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"njmzvasre","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"0jsdkho72","text":"What to Expect at a Tinnitus Appointment"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"k9hy23str","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"mrg7t9f96","text":"A tinnitus visit is not just “pick a hearing aid.” The goal is to understand what is happening and build a plan that works for you."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"e7cuvgrgn","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"1g8qko11q","text":"Step 1: Getting to Know You"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"zfp5stboa","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"94lke2y16","text":"We ask questions like:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"ic5qdsbuy","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"blmur0jq4","text":"When did tinnitus start?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"regz73pdy","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"hm4yugybq","text":"Is it in one ear or both?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"gntdxz4o2","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"34ubvrcrc","text":"Is it constant or off and on?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"6o1fo41ak","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"mirqocms5","text":"What makes it worse or better?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"cp9pdu8xw","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"knuypv511","text":"How is your sleep?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"lh3s11tum","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"nz153fle5","text":"How is your stress?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"6e9yepefe","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"pgv0uw28p","text":"Any noise exposure history?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"1ycbaatyq","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"fpgtqmznc","text":"Step 2: Ear Exam"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"e6ofex585","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"6cj4rgf5f","text":"We check for:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"zfuy72yqj","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"ftsmq9f2q","text":"Earwax buildup"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"fbd0rmu4i","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"jjcfasp4j","text":"Signs of infection"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"uvbzaj0gl","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"5uv471bmg","text":"Blockage or irritation"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"gdbvk1b5l","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"tz3enpnk1","text":"Step 3: Hearing Testing"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"a7h4shojk","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"k8sm877zp","text":"A hearing test helps us see if hearing loss is part of the picture. This matters because hearing loss is one of the top reasons tinnitus happens."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"65i2eaxzl","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"oqqv0u99n","text":"Step 4: A Clear Plan"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"tbzj56rrt","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"4ikrf5ywe","text":"If hearing aids are a good fit, we explain options. If something else seems likely, we may recommend medical follow-up, too."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"auif1jfzu","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"8d9x5dxgf","text":"How Hearing Aids Are Fitted for Tinnitus"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"uelyihshp","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"npaledggh","text":"If you choose hearing aids, fitting is important. Hearing aids must be adjusted to your hearing needs and your comfort."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"nen2enwk3","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"19cdumdco","text":"During your fitting, you can expect:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"96soz1os9","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"lg7yrsui9","text":"Programming based on your hearing test"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"bx3re6zjw","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"vn7ph6ign","text":"Comfort checks (so nothing feels too tight)"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"61myo8sny","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s8tlddeqk","text":"Feedback checks (to prevent whistling)"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"yv1tl4o8u","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"csph0ev8h","text":"Tinnitus feature setup if your devices include it"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"yvqrd72lf","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"0ab7elvmb","text":"Real-life listening tips for home and work"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"jubu0uokf","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"wvu89eszp","text":"Then we schedule follow-ups because tinnitus relief and hearing comfort often improve with small fine-tuning changes."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"a987ftxep","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"5s63smgjh","text":"How Long Does It Take to Adjust?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"762tcoxnv","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"o7itfk27g","text":"Many people notice changes quickly, sometimes the same day. But adjustment can take time, too."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"3ox3xn0hp","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"lt2lizwqe","text":"It is normal if:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"8gmfbo9ra","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"m1ha9y0g5","text":"Your own voice sounds different at first"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"79b4351hr","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"05kxseuhx","text":"Every day sounds seem sharper"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"e4fdkoox8","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"70zt0dr7l","text":"You need a few follow-ups to fine-tune settings"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"5trk2prqp","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"b70mq1hzh","text":"Your brain is learning how to process clearer sound again. With consistent wear, most people adapt well."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"cl7t5m282","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"51r1pofj4","text":"Other Helpful Tools Alongside Hearing Aids"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"il251jykx","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"p0nlm094l","text":"Hearing aids can be a big help, but tinnitus care often works best as a “toolbox.” Other tools may include:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"o43yz0j68","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"s1xx99f7v","text":"Sound Enrichment at Night"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"sbs65q1hz","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"ut7ac9qd3","text":"A fan, white noise machine, or soft sound app can make bedtime easier."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"fp5t69c6v","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"nzncrdci4","text":"Stress Management"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"07ih8t5yw","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"94e34e2s5","text":"Stress can increase tinnitus. Simple steps like breathing exercises, walking, or gentle stretching can help."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"ow4ukuw3s","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"bdxppc4gd","text":"Better Sleep Habits"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"lvbp9a82g","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"baa8v55u1","text":"Poor sleep makes tinnitus feel louder. A steady bedtime routine can reduce tinnitus distress."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"u3eq95pe4","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"wg7iq4d20","text":"Hearing Protection"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"qrboda2tb","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"tzn4imh5z","text":"Protect your ears from loud sounds. Hearing protection is important, but wearing earplugs all day in normal sound can sometimes make tinnitus feel louder. We can guide you on smart use."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"qnuzx97eh","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"2d3wfozv0","text":"Medical Referral When Needed"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"mzezl92ne","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"pt9hbn7ef","text":"If tinnitus is sudden, only in one ear, comes with dizziness, or seems pulse-like, you should get a medical evaluation. We can help guide you for the next steps."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"loc3qr2oo","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"d4l9nv7jy","text":"Common Questions People Ask About Hearing Aids for Tinnitus"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"jyad8q9xh","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"nj5asnapk","text":"Will hearing aids stop tinnitus completely?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"8le63q9q4","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"0na2svuzv","text":"Not always. But many people notice tinnitus is less noticeable and less stressful when they hear better and use sound therapy features."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"6f910bnmv","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"qgztitidq","text":"What if I only have tinnitus and no hearing loss?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"cm78q5trh","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"xz3j4ykmd","text":"Some people still benefit from sound therapy devices or counseling strategies. A hearing test helps decide the best option."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"bsxyg84lo","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"73v4ulx2g","text":"Do I have to wear hearing aids all day for tinnitus relief?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"c55cmaefa","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"9ltkxcfrl","text":"Most people get the best results with regular wear. The more your brain gets steady sound input, the better tinnitus blending usually works."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"gcng4qlqr","style":"h3","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"8fyxye4jm","text":"Can hearing aids make tinnitus worse?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"t29dm6t1f","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"lgcr3ij8p","text":"When fitted correctly, they should not. Poor programming or overly loud settings can cause discomfort, which is why professional fitting and follow-up matter."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"yrwumnjnd","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"ei8i7crdw","text":"When You Should Get Help Right Away"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"nikmyke3q","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"4advdoj9u","text":"While tinnitus is often not dangerous, contact a healthcare provider promptly if you have:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"vq9r0srff","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"e004g2gcz","text":"Sudden hearing loss"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"weq1bs7il","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"92dlbs1sk","text":"Tinnitus in only one ear that is new"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"prmueowdz","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"a4xgsid61","text":"Severe dizziness or spinning"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"mrly6bg1i","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"0rbumtnky","text":"Ear pain, drainage, or fever"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"8oc4hxmvg","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"n1cagos1p","text":"A pulsing sound that matches your heartbeat"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"eavlv2d70","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"vwnzomwpe","text":"These symptoms can signal issues that need medical evaluation."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"nqtqun9fo","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"xgk1eo2y0","text":"Why Choose Maico Audiology in Virginia?"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"gwnrdlvpw","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"h2pc3jfq9","text":"At Maico Audiology, we believe tinnitus care should feel personal, calm, and clear. We help patients:"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"qq6xhjgvn","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"2wvw327pn","text":"Understand what tinnitus means for their hearing health"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"gy6ecc05v","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"ljan31al4","text":"Get accurate testing and answers"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"03oemd77n","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"b34y54vab","text":"Explore hearing aids with tinnitus relief options"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"6xcwm59kl","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"jr2c0hq94","text":"Learn simple daily strategies that make tinnitus easier to live with"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"erqu1o6oj","style":"normal","listItem":"bullet","level":1,"children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"gdows5r9d","text":"Get follow-up care and ongoing support"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"oyl7arxnw","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"4uyybjw2e","text":"We proudly serve patients in Newport News, Smithfield, and Chesapeake, VA, and we’re here to guide you step by step."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"7oowsera9","style":"h2","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"7bsmrlsa4","text":"A Simple Next Step"}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"vmi52te7j","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"kaghsqnmm","text":"Tinnitus can be exhausting. It can interrupt sleep, make quiet moments feel stressful, and make it harder to focus. The good news is you do not have to figure it out alone. With the right plan, many people feel real improvement."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"3wbv19qns","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"jvyisflu0","text":"If you are ready to explore hearing aids for tinnitus, start with a professional hearing evaluation. The right information leads to the right solution. At Maico Audiology, we’ll listen to your concerns, explain your results in a clear way, and help you choose the best path forward."}]},{"_type":"block","_key":"nlv1japd2","style":"normal","children":[{"_type":"span","_key":"gjdx9xmxv","text":"And remember: hearing aids for tinnitus are not just about sound. They are about comfort, confidence, and feeling more like yourself again."},{"_type":"span","_key":"4cism64tg","text":"Schedule an appointment","marks":["pln5pi636"]},{"_type":"span","_key":"d5patua6d","text":"today!"}],"markDefs":[{"_type":"link","_key":"pln5pi636","href":"/book-appointment/","blank":false}]}],"featured_image":{"id":"01KS5SXCHRG7NVSX295207XD5H","provider":"local","filename":"assets__media__Hearing-Aids-for-Tinnitus-How-They-Help-You-Find-Relief-and-Hear-Better-08101a26a3.jpg","mimeType":"image/jpeg","alt":"","meta":{"storageKey":"01KS5SXCF3QFE8J8R6RRKARNTV.jpg","caption":null,"blurhash":"LiNw1hRj-p%2~Ct7J7jtNbayjFWU","dominantColor":"rgb(194,190,191)"}},"meta_title":"Hearing Aids for Tinnitus | Maico Audiological Services","meta_description":"Hearing aids for tinnitus can improve hearing and help reduce ringing in the ears. Visit Maico Audiology to connect with expert audiologists in Virginia.","_slug":"hearing-aids-for-tinnitus"}',NULL,'2026-05-21 22:54:18');
